HEADWORD: homeothermic
<hw>homeothermic</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>having constant and relatively high body
temperature; warm-blooded; same as <er>homoiothermal</er>; -- of birds
and mammals. Contrasted to <ant>poikilothermal</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> homoiothermic, homoiothermal, homothermic,
homothermal.</syn>⟦br⟧
